cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper discusses a model of pedestrian motion which involves multiple agents and their interactions. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the movement of pedestrians in a spatially discrete model, which can be seen as a network of cells. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the optimization of a system (pedestrian motion model) in terms of symmetry and computational efficiency. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a method for implementing heterogeneously distributed walking speeds, which can be seen as an AI technique. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper examines different neighborhoods for different walking speeds and proposes criteria for finding an optimal neighborhood, which involves algorithmic considerations.
